Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Euphranor. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 512.02.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0725)
